    "THE BENGAL HURKARU The importance of all these subjects will I feel confident be yeadily admitted by persons ofevery party and the right ofth House of Assembly to enqvire intothem is undoubted being un founded on the Canada Bill passed inthe 31st year of his pre sent Majestys reign The House too proceeded in the discussion with great temper and moderation Although advised by som ofthe members to withhold the supply till the enquiry was ter minated the majority of the House would not anticipate the arbitrary preceedings of the Lieutenant Governor but said tha it would be better he should incur any disgrace that could attach tosuch proceedings than that he should have it in his powei to charge the House of Assembly with expressing any doubt of the good faith of the Provincial Government The supply which for the revenues of the Province was enormous was according _granted without inquiry and as afterwards tarned out upon a very fallacious estimate submitted to the House by the Lieute nantG overnor While the enquiry subsequently entered into was going on the Goveruor came down to the House and in the following speech the insulting irony of which caunot be mistaken"
